Title: "Winter's Elegance: The Marbled Guardian" |

Blend of Two (1,2) Styles:

1 Low and Wide Angle Photography, captured on a Sony A7RIII
2 Exquisite Ink-Drawing with a touch of Watercolor Splatter |
Artists:
Mika Asai, Benedick Bana, and Kim Jung Gi |

Theme:
Capture the majesty and grandeur of a White Great Dane, elevating its natural elegance with a unique marbled fur pattern, resembling white marble, all whilst emphasizing the beauty of the snowy winter landscape that it's surrounded by. |

Composition:

Foreground:
Freshly fallen snow, untouched and pristine, sparkles in the soft winter light, creating an almost dreamlike setting. Closer to the viewer, snow-covered ferns and bushes provide a delicate framing, with frozen droplets hanging from the edges, gleaming in the sunlight. |

Centerpiece:
The White Great Dane, its physique majestic and regal, stands with a confident poise amidst the winter wonderland. The marbled fur pattern is intricately detailed with exquisite ink drawing, capturing the swirls and patterns that resemble white marble. The low and wide angle accentuates its powerful stature, making the canine seem almost mythical against the snowy expanse. |

Background:
A serene forest of tall, snow-covered pines stretches out into the horizon, their tops vanishing into a soft mist. The sun, low in the sky, casts a warm, golden hue over the scene, contrasting the cool blues and whites of the snow and creating a surreal, painterly effect. |

Style:
Utilize the Sony A7RIII to capture the breathtaking details of the scene, from the individual snowflakes on the dog's marbled fur to the distant, foggy treeline. The ink drawing technique lends depth and texture to the marbled pattern, while watercolor splatters introduce gentle shades of blues and grays, accentuating the chill of the winter atmosphere. |

Message:
This piece, a collaborative effort of Mika Asai, Benedick Bana, and Kim Jung Gi, invites the viewer into a tranquil winter moment where nature's quiet beauty is juxtaposed against the awe-inspi

Title: "Winter's Elegance: The Marbled Guardian" |



1 Low and Wide Angle Photography, captured on a Sony A7RIII

Mika Asai, Benedick Bana, and Kim Jung Gi |

Theme:
Capture the majesty and grandeur of a White Great Dane, elevating its natural elegance with a unique marbled fur pattern, resembling white marble, all whilst emphasizing the beauty of the snowy winter landscape that it's surrounded by. |

Composition:

Foreground:
Freshly fallen snow, untouched and pristine, sparkles in the soft winter light, creating an almost dreamlike setting. Closer to the viewer, snow-covered ferns and bushes provide a delicate framing, with frozen droplets hanging from the edges, gleaming in the sunlight. |

Centerpiece:
The White Great Dane, its physique majestic and regal, stands with a confident poise amidst the winter wonderland. The marbled fur pattern is intricately detailed with exquisite ink drawing, capturing the swirls and patterns that resemble white marble. The low and wide angle accentuates its powerful stature, making the canine seem almost mythical against the snowy expanse. |

Background:
A serene forest of tall, snow-covered pines stretches out into the horizon, their tops vanishing into a soft mist. The sun, low in the sky, casts a warm, golden hue over the scene, contrasting the cool blues and whites of the snow and creating a surreal, painterly effect. |

Style:
Utilize the Sony A7RIII to capture the breathtaking details of the scene, from the individual snowflakes on the dog's marbled fur to the distant, foggy treeline. The ink drawing technique lends depth and texture to the marbled pattern, while watercolor splatters introduce gentle shades of blues and grays, accentuating the chill of the winter atmosphere. |, photo, wildlife photography
